reviews.review_text:
Track order and number error Excellent show. Jerry ballads from the post-Brent era really shine. China Doll is no exception though It is not a standout compared to its 93, 94 brethren. Despite track list errors this show is well worth down loading- it is a beautiful sound board

But rather than sharing my opinions I am going to list out the actual track list of this show. It is out of order in that Casey Jones has been stuck before China Cat>Rider- and as a result the track names are all wrong in the 2nd set. The first set is fine.

track 11: Crowd Noise
track 12: Casey Jones
track 13: China Cat Sunflower
track 14: I Know You Rider
Track 15: Estimated Prophet
Track 16: Way to go home
track 17: Drums
track 18: Space
track 19: Last Time
track 20: China Doll
track 21: Around&Around

Amazing for '92 This is one of those shows that I can't help but listen to all of the way through. Just a solid performance from the boys. Jerry is in fine form and ready to play. Best latter-era "New Speedway Boogie."

Let the world go by..all lost in dreaming Pretty good sound..voices through the mics is a little distant? I saw over 30 shows in 92' and I was at both of these Deer Creeks..I love this show and it is one of my favorites from the year..Yea Help>Slip>Franklins to open..but what I really love is from To Lay Me Down to Smokestack..off the hook!! The 2nd set is very solid and the Casey Jones!! I caught the one in RFK also but it hadn't been since Merriweather 84' for me to hear this great song again..so please>GIVE IT A WHIRL>Forever Grateful>Forever Dead!!!! Lifer!!
